The specific features of theological Latin from Vulgata until the Reformation period will be studied. Also, the Latin works of the most influential medieval theologians will be introduced.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course for advanced students is to get acquainted with theological Latin on the deeper level (especially in syntax and terminology of Medieval Latin and Neo-Latin) through reading sources, to be able to work with the sources of church history in original language and to use theological terminology capably.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Deeper knowledge of Latin language: 1) through cursory reading of the text with the aid of the dictionary; 2) using the grammar-translation method; 3) analysing the specific features of the syntax of Medieval Latin and Neo-Latin. To get acquainted with the history of theological terminology.
